modules.description: This module defines test execution interfaces for asynchronous test cases, supporting both deferred and synchronous test functions. It works with `Async.Deferred.t` return types, `Cmdliner.Term.t` for command-line configuration, and structured test lists with named test cases. It is used to define and run test suites for asynchronous OCaml code, with support for test speed categorization and configurable timeouts.
